Title: Series: The Seven Wonders of the World
Description: The Lighthouse of Alexandria; a seascape with the enormous tower on an island in the distance labelled "PHAROS"; on the mainland is a city and a snaking bridge leads to the island; in the foreground King Ptolemy converses with an artist; after Maarten de Vos. 1614 Engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Magdalena de Passe
Published by: Crispijn de Passe the Elder
Curator's comments: From a series of seven plates (Hollstein 72-78 ad).
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (77 ad)
Franken 1881 / L'oeuvre gravé des van de Passe (327)
Associated names: Representation of: Ptolemy I Soter I
